title: Borrowed Time
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2ZCa1HG

by grilledcheesing

WARNING — SPOILERS FOR AVENGERS: ENDGAME.

It’s been two years since the final battle with Thanos. On the surface, Peter has everything together. It’s freshman year and he’s interning with Bruce Banner, living with his best friend, and has extended Spider-Man’s radius of superheroism out to Manhattan.

The truth is, though, the busier Peter keeps himself, the less likely it is that anyone will notice he’s falling apart. That is, until he runs into the one person who can cut past his bullshit — a person who is very much supposed to be dead.

blog.name: ironmess
blog.title: au where tony is happy
blog.description: hi im moffatt aka your local bi argie that loves tony stark. i am first and foremost, marvel's bitch

summary: Bro like.... I was sobbing in the theater when Tony died and didn’t stop until the end with Steve where I cried even harder.......
question: Bro like.... I was sobbing in the theater when Tony died and didn’t stop until the end with Steve where I cried even harder.... I thought « wow! Ppl will be going crazy on tumblr on how good this was » and,,,, I come to understand that people will not find the good in anything if there’s a little bad (especially on tumblr) and that makes me so sad y’a know? I love Steve and Peggy, Stuck and Stony but did ppl think the last two would happen? Just be happy y’a know?
answer:
this is exactly how I feel! tumblr can be really really toxic with these things. endgame was a beautiful movie but most importantly, it was a good movie. well written and with complex theme exploration. we are watching a drama, not a romcom or a sitcom. there can’t be happy endings for everyone and it would be really shitty if they were.

marvel kicked the board with this movie. everyone always shitted on marvel because there weren’t any high stakes. every character had plot armor. it was artificial, fake and empty feeling. this movie made marvel more emotional, more real, more heartbreaking. it made us feel more. that’s the mark of an amazing movie.

a part of tumblr will complain about a lot of things and some people will tear this movie apart. I won’t. my friends won’t. you gotta surround yourself with people that make you feel happy, not people that drag you down. I honestly unfollowed a lot of people, but I don’t hold resentment towards them, I just don’t wanna see their content for now.

I wanna celebrate marvel and these 11 years with the best movie I’ve seen in this universe. tony stark, my love, was made a legend and I’m grateful to have lived through it.
